The semifields isotopic to $B(2,m,s,0,t)$ where $s\notin\lbrace 0,m\rbrace$ are precisely those which are
quadratic over the left and the right nucleus (in characteristic $2$).
\end{Proposition}
\begin{proof} The condition on $s$ says  that $K_1$ ( the fixed field
of the automorphism associated to ${\sigma}$ in $L$) is properly contained in $L.$ It can be assumed that
$p_1=1,p_2=0,p_3\in\lbrace 0,1\rbrace .$
